All editors have either changed cx to in or changed lectiunculis to spectiunculis. But the ms. reading as given above is right. What Cicero means is this: he. had said above that the leisure of Marius (gained by absenting himself from the games) would not be rightly employed unless he did something useful. Now to take ‘ little dips into books ’ might fairly be called useful as compared with dozing over hackneyed farces.
